  "description": "<p>\n\t<a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/zt/bbclearningenglish/\" style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://i2.w.hjfile.cn/doc/201507/c6e5c0306433433eb4a3dcf14ae6a467.jpg\" width=\"100%\" /></a></p>\n<p>\n\t<img src=\"http://i2.w.hjfile.cn/doc/201601/8de271436b534f6abae3256222b6c8bc.jpg\" /></p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>今日短语</strong></p>\n<p>\n\t一个能够起到警示作用的事件就可以被称为 &ldquo;a wake-up call，警钟 &rdquo;。为的是警告一个人避免重犯同样错误或防止将来出现更大问题。</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>例句</strong></p>\n<p>\n\t<em>The plane crash was a wake-up call for airlines never to compromise on safety.</em></p>\n<p>\n\t<em>When I failed my mock exam it was a real wake-up call. From then on I studied and revised hard.</em></p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>请注意</strong></p>\n<p>\n\t如果你突然发现什么不好的事情已经发生了或者正在进行中，这种情况可以用&ldquo;wake up to the fact&rdquo;来表达，意思是觉醒、醒悟过来。</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>例句</strong></p>\n<p>\n\t<em>You need to wake up to the fact that you are not going to pass your exams if you don&rsquo;t start working harder.</em></p>\n<p>\n\t<em>It took a while for my parents to wake up to the fact that their business was failing.</em></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">\n\t<img src=\"http://i2.w.hjfile.cn/doc/201507/96d23c9b2d084a4e8c878ed4f9937b90.jpg\" style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\" width=\"100%\" /></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 25.2px;\">\n\t<span style=\"color: rgb(153, 153, 153); font-size: 12px; line-height: 25.2px;\">声明：&nbsp;本文由BBC英语教学授权沪江英语发布。任何媒体禁止转载。</span></p>\n<br /><center><a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p764071/#relate_articles\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_chat.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p764071\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_digg.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a></center><h3 style=\"margin: 10px;\">本周最热文章</h3><ul style=\"margin: 5px 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p763826/\">1只喵和3只哈士奇组成家庭后张张表情有毒！</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20p